Europeans confusion on burgers is so beyond me. A burger is ground meat formed into a patty it has nothing to do with the bun. You can eat a turkey burger on sliced white bread and the actual patty is still considered a burger therefore the sandwich is a burger. If it's not a ground Patty it is a sandwich especially if it is chicken it's a sandwich. Also sliders are small sandwiches regardless if it's a ground meat patty or not it's still called a slider if it's on a small bun. So if you have chicken breast, they're called chicken sliders. I see you guys call anything that has a hamburger bun a burger. A chicken sandwich is not a burger unless you grind it and make a patty out of it, then it's not a burger. It's a chicken burger. I see where it could be confusing but the basis is the fact that a burger is a ground patty. That's literally the only thing Europeans have to understand.. If it's not a ground Patty it's a sandwich, And if it's a small bun it's a slider
